<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-02T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-02T23:00:00-05:00" n="355" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/717: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Neville</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-03T11:00:00+07:00">April 3, 1940—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 3—3:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>15. The Foreign Office has been approached by the Japanese press for
                                a statement in regard to Wang Ching Wei government. Reply will be
                                non-committal. The Prime Minister told me today that this country
                                will not have relations with it.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Neville</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>